                    <comment id="12451849" author="manawiz" created="Wed, 22 Nov 2006 02:27:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With this could also come negative-only queries, e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-foo&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as a shortcut for&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;:&lt;/b&gt; -foo&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12451861" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 22 Nov 2006 06:16:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the patch....  &lt;b&gt;:&lt;/b&gt; means MatchAllDocsQuery&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since it required a grammar change I made it allow &quot;*&quot; as a fieldname (so one could do *:foo).&lt;br/&gt;
This allows one to come up with a specialized syntax for searching across multiple fields by simply subclassing QueryParser methods.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
